comments.body:
@axamei The last two commits fix the visual regressions. 

Explanation:
The `/deep/` selector does not work with "functional" components, which provide much faster rendering. The spacing issues in Approvals are the application css overwriting the non-scoped css, so that should be fixed in the Approvals app. Also, to correct for the removal of `/deep/`, I created a `style` attribute for tag-items so we can apply the pill to the Approvals cards in a PR to that repo. 

Unless I'm missing something, I don't think we can prevent a breaking change when trying to accommodate  the changes required in the functional component work. I will update the semver appropriately when releasing. LMK what you think, and merge if you are 👍 .

marc_liberation.title: Introduces handling for case where Oracle DB query errors are raised while retrieving bib. IDs related to request IDs

comments.body: @hackmastera Cool!  We were just closing or merging PRs prior to making the update.  Good to know the script exists.

The pagination was ordering the events in a DESC order; as a result the latest created event was on top of the page. 
The rake task was getting from the events page response the last event that happened to be on the same page and at the end (bottom) of the page. 
We need to make sure when we apply the pagination that we will adjust all the rake tasks that look for an event to be the correct event based on the **order** of the pagination and across the **pages** of the pagination.
example task: https://github.com/pulibrary/marc_liberation/blob/356503c58ab51eb7dcf53f79b190dd7cb01f05de/lib/tasks/orangeindex.rake#L148
